TASK_PACKET

Packet ID
CRUSHR-FORMAT-09

Title
Phase-9 corruption grid and survivability evaluation harness

Objective
Introduce a structured corruption matrix (“grid”) that exercises the crushr
recovery model across multiple independent damage dimensions.

This packet expands the salvage experiment framework and reporting model.
It does not modify the archive format.

Scope
- corruption grid specification
- corruption operators
- grid execution harness
- enhanced classification reporting
- CLI command
- experiment outputs
- test coverage

Out of Scope
- archive format changes
- metadata placement strategy (FORMAT-08)
- compression algorithm changes
- block structure changes

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

BACKGROUND

Earlier phases evaluated corruption using coarse region failures:

- header damage
- index damage
- payload damage
- tail truncation

These tests validated the basic survivability architecture.

However, FORMAT-07 introduced graph-aware recovery reasoning and finer
recovery classes. The existing corruption suite is now too coarse to
exercise the new reasoning capabilities.

Phase-9 introduces a structured corruption grid to test how different
“truth layers” and payload topologies interact during recovery.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

GRID MODEL

The corruption matrix is defined by four axes.

Axis A — Truth layer damage

These scenarios simulate loss of specific metadata layers.

A1 header corruption
A2 index corruption
A3 manifest corruption
A4 path checkpoint corruption
A5 manifest + path corruption
A6 index + manifest corruption

Axis B — Payload damage

These scenarios simulate block-level failures.

B0 none
B1 single block deletion
B2 sparse block deletion (every Nth block)
B3 clustered block deletion
B4 block reorder
B5 block duplication

Axis C — Damage topology

These scenarios describe spatial distribution of corruption.

C1 single contiguous region
C2 two independent regions
C3 scattered corruption
C4 region + metadata layer damage

Axis D — Dataset class

Reuse existing datasets:

D1 smallfiles
D2 mixed
D3 largefiles

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

SCENARIO GENERATION

The grid is not executed as a full combinatorial explosion.

Instead a curated matrix is defined.

Initial Phase-9 test set:

target scenario count: ~48

Examples:

smallfiles_manifest_corruption_single_block
smallfiles_manifest_corruption_sparse_blocks
mixed_index_manifest_corruption_clustered
largefiles_block_reorder_two_regions
mixed_manifest_path_corruption_sparse
largefiles_sparse_deletion_scattered

Scenarios must include a reproducible RNG seed.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

NEW CORRUPTION OPERATORS

The harness must implement the following operators.

delete_random_block
remove a verified payload block

delete_every_nth_block
remove blocks at regular interval

delete_cluster
remove contiguous block region

reorder_blocks
shuffle block order in archive

duplicate_block
insert duplicate block payload

manifest_corruption
damage manifest structure

path_checkpoint_corruption
damage path record surface

Operators must be deterministic when seeded.

